===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|شَوّالٌ}}''' {{IPAchar|(šáwwal)}} {{m}}

#[[Shawwal]], the tenth of the twelve months of the Muslim lunar calendar, each beginning with a [[new moon]]. [[Shawwal]] means [[raised]] in Arabic, because the she-camels begin to raise their tails during this time after giving birth.

